reviewText: Hard workout, but you can choose the components that work best for you.  It's great the way she tells you the next move coming up so you're not always trying to catch up to the moves on the screen.  Many of the moves build, meaning you start with something that doesn't seem to hard, and then she adds a "bit of a challenge".  If you can do it you feel so proud, rather than some DVDs that make you feel like the one that always got picked last for dodge ball in gym class. Also great to have the countdown timer on the screen the whole time!
This was a great buy and definitely was every helpful in getting me toned.

Have tried a lot of diets and weight loss plans but the SparkPeople resources are the best ....Coach Nicole is easy to follow and not a screaming drill Sargent you find in most exercise tapes. She is a young breath of fresh air!
These videos have something for everyone. I can mix and things up so that I'm not bored with the same routine!
Great workouts. Easy to follow. She really directs you and gives you heads up when changing moves. Really works out the whole body.

Work out routines are great, gives several options of level of workout. My only complaint is having to select with each part of the workout, not being able to set it up ahead to 1. warm up, 2. work out, 3. cool down.

These workouts are beginner/intermediate, but somehow I'm always very sweaty when I get done. They're low impact, and I find them to be pretty interesting. I don't care for the schedule that comes with them, they seem to have thought that if you're intermediate or advanced that you suddenly have time to workout for an hour or more a day.
workouts start slow but build up.  really a great work out.
Coach Nicole is the best, really good instruction and it works.
fantastic work out video . coach Nichol is awesome.
